{
  "texts": [
    "While this \"divide-and-conquer\" approach can cover the complexity of long sequences, it increases the computational complexity given the number of transformers used to handle each part of this hierarchy.",
    "• At the level of the internal transformer architecture (R1b): In this case, the architecture formulation is modified to receive different data streams (Fouladvand et al. 2021).",
    "The main advantage is that outputs capture the associations between input streams, represented as attention weights between different tokens across such streams.",
    "This approach preserves the original semantics of each stream while the network units handle them.",
    "However, the weakness of this approach is the exponential complexity regarding the number of streams since each stream must interact with all other streams."
  ]
}